## Astro 6 — Breaking Changes to Watch For
ViewTransitions  → ClientRouter from astro:transitions
z from astro:content → z from astro/zod
z from astro:schema  → z from astro/zod
Node.js requirement: 22+ (not 18, not 20)

---

## Performance
- Astro ships zero JS by default — maintain this
- client:load only when JS is truly essential
- Prefer client:idle (after page load) or client:visible (on scroll into view)
- Use <Image /> from astro:assets for all images
- Lazy load below-the-fold content

---

## Accessibility
- Semantic HTML: <section>, <article>, <nav>, <main>, <header>, <footer>
- All images: descriptive alt text (alt="" for decorative)
- One <h1> per page, then h2, h3 in order — no skipping levels
- Keyboard navigation must work for all interactive elements
- Color contrast: 4.5:1 minimum for body text
- ARIA labels on interactive elements without visible text

